s a pleasure to meet you, and also to hear a bit about your own work on kinship. I have one preliminary comment to make, which is that everything I say now is from memory, and my memory is not brilliant. If there\rquote 
s any discrepancy between what I say and anything that\rquote s written down \endash  for example, in the preface to the Elmdon book or whatever, then the written word should take precedence. So w
hat I recall now is very supplementary, and really is nothing more than that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid857456\charrsid857456 
