\par Elaine:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid857456\charrsid857456 Going back to status, I find that very interesting. But I\rquote 
m relating back in terms of who belong and so on. I like your analysis in the Elmdon book, that although birthplace looks like a simple reference to locality, in fact the issue of birth is the is
sue of family origin. So what is important is not where a person is born, but where their family roots are supposed to be. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid857456\charrsid857456 
