\par Marilyn:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid857456\charrsid857456 Well, only in the sense that - I mean I don\rquote t speak of my life, but for example, there are pictures there of Petts Wood, that I
\rquote ve already mentioned, and I am trying to convey kinship in a very specific location, which is middle class English. Although middle class English, I would also locate in this broad category of \'93Euro-American\'94
, by which I mean post-Enlightenment educated middle class discourse that has particular views about nature and culture and so on and so forth, and I can go into that. So a lot of the materials were drawn from my experience. So, for example \endash 
 I mean, this is highly eclectic \endash  but there\rquote s both Jane Austen and Darwin in there. Well, Jane Austen\rquote s in there because my mother just loved Jane Austen. Darwin is
 in there because my father read a lot in biology and evolution, and so forth. I mean, that kind of thing, the materials are, by and large, quite familiar to me. So perhaps \'93familiarity\'94 is better than the word \'93autobiographical\'94. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid857456\charrsid857456 
